本論文永久網址:      Twitter研究生:賴見強研究生(外文):Lai Chien Chiang論文名稱:兩岸國際私法中最重要牽連關係原則之研究論文名稱(外文):Study on the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship  of Conflict of Laws in Taiwan and Mainland China指導教授:張元宵博士口試委員:黃陽壽教授、尹章華教授口試日期:2014-07-02學位類別:碩士校院名稱:東吳大學系所名稱:法律學系學門:法律學門學類:一般法律學類論文出版年:2014畢業學年度:102語文別:中文論文頁數:216中文關鍵詞:最重要牽連關係原則、國際私法、法律衝突、涉外民事法律適用法、涉外民事法律關係適用法外文關鍵詞:Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship、Conflict of Laws、Private International Law相關次數:

被引用:0點閱:468評分:下載:42書目收藏:0



自一九七一年『美國法律學會』完成美國國際私法第二新編，在哥倫比亞大學教授Willis  L. M. Reese 教授的力倡下，「最重要牽連關係原則」(the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship)成為美國國際私法第二新編之核心理論，又有稱之為最密切牽連關係理論、最強牽連關係理論或最真實牽連關係理論等等。。於此之後，「最重要牽連關係原則」成為國際私法上極為重要之原則，其後許多國家之國際私法亦採用最重要牽連關係原則，分處海峽兩岸之臺灣地區及大陸地區亦然。2011年5月26日正式生效，臺灣地區新國際私法(涉外民事法律適用法)正式生效，該法第2條、第4條、第5條、第17條至第20條、第25條、第28條、第43條至第45條、第47條、第48條及第50條等條文，均與「最重要牽連關係原則」有關，臺灣地區新法可謂大量採納「最重要牽連關係原則」。大陸地區亦自2011年4月1日起施行涉外民事法律關係適用法，從大陸地區於新法中第2條明文規定：「涉外民事關係適用的法律，依照本法確定。其他法律對涉外民事關係法律適用另有特別規定的，依照其規定。本法和其他法律對涉外民事關係法律適用沒有規定的，適用與該涉外民事關係有最密切聯繫的法律。」、第6條規定：「涉外民事關係適用外國法律，該國不同區域實施不同法律的，適用與該涉外民事關係有最密切聯繫區域的法律。」益見大陸地區新國際私法對「最重要牽連關係原則」之重視。故自兩岸新國際私法之立法內容觀之，即可發現兩岸之新國際私法，均不約而同的採納最重要牽連關係原則作為修法或立法之指導原則，最重要牽連關係原則顯然已在兩岸之國際私法中具有舉足輕重之地位，有進一步研究探討之意義。故本文爰依最重要牽連關係原則為中心，探討其在兩岸新國際私法之發展。

The “American Law Institute (ALI)”completed the compilation of the Restatement “Second”, Conflict of Laws in 1971. As strongly proposed by Professor Willis L. M. Reese of Columbia University, the “ Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship” became the core theory of the Second Restatement, also known as the “theory of the closest connection” or “theory of the strongest connection” and, possibly, other paraphrasing. Sometime thereafter, the “Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship” became an extremely significant principle in the Private International Law. Such same phenomenon is equally existent on both sides of the Taiwan Strait, i.e., Taiwan and China.In Taiwan, the latest Private International Law (i.e., the Act Governing the Choice of Law in Civil Matters Involving Foreign Elements) officially came into effect on May 26, 2011.  Under the said Act, the contents set forth under Articles 2, 4, 5, 17~20, 25, 28, 43~45, 47, 48 and 50 are closely linked up with “the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship”.  To put it in more understandable terms, in the new ACT now in force in territories of Taiwan, the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship has been heavily adopted.In China, the “Law of the Application of Law for Foreign-related Civil Relations” was officially put into force on April 1, 2011.  As expressly provided for in Article 2 of the new Act: “If there are no provisions in this Law or other laws on the application of any laws concerning foreign-related civil relations, the laws which have the closest relation with this foreign- related civil relation shall be appled.” Further as expressly provided for in Article 6 of the same Law: “As for the application of foreign laws on a foreign-related civil relation, if different laws are enforced in different regions of this foreign country, the laws of the region which has the closest relation with this foreign- related civil relation shall be appled.” These facts further indicate the increasingly important role “the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship” plays amidst the new Private International Law prevailing in China.Judging from the contents of the new Private International Laws in force on both sides of Taiwan Strait, we would notice that both Taiwan and China have simultaneously adopted the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship as the guiding principles of enactment or amendment.  Very apparently, “the Doctrine of the Most Significant Relationship” has played virtually the pivotal role in the development of modern International Private Law in both Taiwan and China and, consequently, deserves further efforts for study.

